Cyberpunk style: A frustrated traveler sits alone in a neon-lit airport terminal at night, bathed in harsh pink and cyan light from glowing holographic WiFi signal icons that flicker and glitch around them. Their laptop screen displays an endless cascade of error windows and authentication dialogs, reflected in the rain-streaked floor-to-ceiling windows. In the background, massive digital billboards advertise connectivity services while the actual signal bars above them spark and malfunction. The scene captures digital alienation—surrounded by promises of connection yet completely isolated. Circuit board patterns are subtly embedded in the terminal's architecture, and tangled fiber optic cables snake along the ceiling like technological vines. The mood is equal parts absurdist and melancholic, with the lone figure dwarfed by towering screens showing spinning loading wheels that never resolve.
